Ebola Hemorrhagic Fever Death Toll Continues to Rise
----------------------------------------------------
KAMPALA: The death toll in Uganda's Ebola hemorrhagic fever epidemic [has
risen to 149 since the disease broke out in mid-September, with 4 more
people dying on Mon 27 Nov 2000, the Health Ministry said. Some 140 of the
victims are from the northern district of Gulu, where the epidemic was
first reported. The disease has killed 4 people in the western town of
Mbarara, and another 5 in the northern Masindi district. Some 367 people
in Uganda are known to have contracted Ebola hemorrhagic fever since
mid-September.
--
H. Larry Penning, M.D.
<lpenning@yahoo.com>
[As of Fri 24 Nov 2000, the WHO figure for laboratory-confirmed cases was
344, of whom 124 had died. - Mod.CP
